Caveats:
1. 'Suppressed' is displayed for data values when they must not be provided in order to protect personal privacy. Data is
suppressed if fewer than 16 cases are reported in any one line of the results table. Data for the "Asian / Pacific Islander",
"American Indian or Alaska Native", and the "Other Races Combined" race categories are suppressed at the Metropolitan
Statistical Area level for populations less than 50,000 persons. Data are suppressed at the state level for certain race and
ethnicity groups: 1) American Indian or Alaska Native data are suppressed at the state level for Delaware, Illinois, Kansas,
Kentucky, New Jersey, and New York; 2) Asian or Pacific Islander data are suppressed at the state level for Delaware, Kansas,
and Kentucky; 3) Hispanic data are supressed at the state level for Delaware, Kentucky, Massachusetts, North Dakota,
Pennsylvania, and Virginia. More information: http://wonder.cdc.gov/wonder/help/cancer-v2013.html#Confidentiality.
2. 'Missing' is displayed for a combination of states/territories/MSAs and years that did not meet the United States Cancer
Statistics (USCS) publication standard or did not allow permission for their data to be used.
3. The "Show Totals" checkbox is disabled when data are grouped by Cancer Sites or by Childhood Cancer, because aggregate
values are displayed in the table. Also be aware that charts and maps containing both aggregate and detail data could be
misleading.
4. These MSAs are missing data for the indicated years: Chattanooga, TN-GA 1999-2002; Denver-Aurora-Lakewood, CO 1999-2001;
Jackson, MS 1999-2002; Kansas City, MO-KS 1999-2013; Knoxville, TN 1999-2002; Las Vegas-Henderson-Paradise, NV 2011-2013; Little
Rock-North Little Rock-Conway, AR 1999-2000; Memphis, TN-MS-AR 1999-2002; Minneapolis-St. Paul-Bloomington, MN-WI 1999-2013;
Nashville-Davidson-Murfreesboro-Franklin, TN 1999-2002; Richmond, VA 1999-2002; Urban Honolulu, HI 1999; Virginia
Beach-Norfolk-Newport News, VA-NC 1999-2002; Washington-Arlington-Alexandria, DC-VA-MD-WV 1999-2002; Wichita, KS 1999-2013.
5. Data are from selected statewide and metropolitan area cancer registries that meet data quality criteria. Incidence data
shown for the United States are diagnoses and populations from included registries only.
6. Information on primary site, behavior, and histology was coded according to the International Classification of Diseases for
Oncology, Third Edition (ICD-O-3) and categorized according to the revised SEER recodes dated January 27, 2003, which define
standard groupings of primary cancer sites.
7. For the 2005 year, the Census Bureau estimates that 203,937 persons were displaced from Alabama, Louisiana, Mississippi and
Texas due to Hurricanes Katrina and Rita. CDC WONDER does not include the displaced persons in the 2005 population counts for
these states, nor are these counts included in the summary populations for the affected division, regions or national
population. However, the USCS web site does include these displaced persons in the national population figures for 2005.
